description:
Smoke-walk item 28 follow-up (parent slice tuxlink-zdfj CLOSED, verified HOLDS for plain text + 6 registered forms). Audit wf_2b5b6659 found a structural gap: Winlink form messages rendered via the WebviewFormViewer fallback (src/mailbox/MessageView.tsx:240-247 — forms NOT in the native registry but with a Viewer HTML template) paint their body in a SEPARATE native Tauri child Webview pixel-positioned over an aria-hidden placeholder div (WebviewFormViewer.tsx). window.print() only captures the MAIN webview DOM, so the OS-level child-webview overlay is NOT in the printout. For these messages the printed page shows the header block followed by an EMPTY box where the form content should be — exactly the 'doesn't print the actual message contents' class of defect item 28 raised, surviving for the unregistered-form-via-webview tail.

NEEDS DESIGN (route through a design brainstorm/BRF before build). Options to evaluate:
(1) route print for webview-form messages through a DOM-rendered KeyValueView/static-HTML representation of the form fields;
(2) have the Rust side print the served Viewer template directly (Tauri webview print API);
(3) snapshot the child webview to an image and inject into the printable DOM.
The 6 registered forms (ics213/ics309/checkin/bulletin/damage_assessment/position) render via in-DOM React ViewComponents and print correctly — gap is the unregistered-form-via-webview path only.

The defensive guard added in Task 1 of P0 (commit 38f0020) reads:

if (!entry || !entry.Form) {
  // Unknown form ID or view-only form (shouldn't happen since the picker
  // is scoped to composableForms()).
  setFormMode({ kind: 'plain' });
  return null;
}

The setFormMode call fires during render. React 18 tolerates same-component setState-during-render (it bails out and re-renders) but emits a development-mode warning. After Tasks 3-5 the registry contains entries where Form is undefined (Position, ICS-309, Damage Assessment) → the guard is now actually reachable via the draft-restore corner case (cf. tuxlink-poai), so the warning will fire in development builds whenever an operator opens a stale form-mode draft.

Refactor: move the reset-formMode-to-plain logic into a useEffect that runs when lookupForm(formMode.formId) returns unsuitable. The render branch then returns null cleanly without setState.

Pre-existing pattern (was present before P0 with 'if (!entry)' only); not a P0 regression. Polish for later, filed for forensics.

Surfaced by final code reviewer dahlia-heron-spruce 2026-05-31.
